.TH "sanitize_state" 9 "sanitize_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sanitize_state \- Resolves implicitly necessary additional changes to a state transition
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "union drbd_state" sanitize_state
.BI "(struct drbd_device *device "  ","
.BI "union drbd_state os "  ","
.BI "union drbd_state ns "  ","
.BI "enum sanitize_state_warnings *warn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
DRBD device.
.IP "os" 12
old state.
.IP "ns" 12
new state.
.IP "warn" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When we loose connection, we have to set the state of the peers disk (pdsk)
to D_UNKNOWN. This rule and many more along those lines are in this function.
